{"questionId":"22460478","questionHtml":"<p>The curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>4</mn></math> is rotated <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mo>°</mo></math> about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis to form a solid of revolution.</p>\n<p>Find the volume of the solid formed.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to express <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>) in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> if base <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math> is applied to both sides.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math> be the volume of the solid formed</